<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Installing the WordPress Theme</div><div><br /></div><div># We will be using the Theme called “wikiWP” from <a href="https://wikiwp.com/">https://wikiwp.com/</a></div><div>Step 1: Download the Theme from <a href="https://wordpress.org/themes/wikiwp/">https://wordpress.org/themes/wikiwp/</a></div><div>            and save anywhere on you local PC ( i.e. ~/tmp )</div><div>Step 2: Login the Wordpress as an Admin</div><div>             <a href="http://wiki.karshi.ca/wp-admin/">http://wiki.karshi.ca/wp-admin/</a></div><div>             User: khasanov</div><div>            Password: H******3</div><div>            Go to the Appearnace and click on “Themes”</div><div>             <en-media hash="151792a8af3f738a3f48d811e639a9fb" type="image/png" /><br /></div><div>             </div><div>             then “Add New” and “Upload Theme"</div><div><br /></div><div>             <en-media hash="cf13f5cb753d1e2a116296329873ca56" type="image/png" /><br /></div><div><br /></div><div>            <en-media hash="b7b17ca6866787c5a2a2055fea0ecb99" type="image/png" /><br /></div><div><br /></div><div>            Browse for the Theme you just downloaded and choose the file</div><div><br /></div><div>            <en-media hash="d95127b0bc15a0756a9b342755c22586" type="image/png" /><br /></div><div><br /></div><div>            </div><div>            <en-media hash="74d29a959582e264e7a32646f0554841" type="image/png" /><br /></div><div><br /></div><div>             Click on “Activate” to activate the Theme</div><div># This will install the Theme under the <span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);">WP_Install_Dir/wp-content/themes</span></div><div># In my case its under:<span style="color: rgb(148, 17, 0);"> /opt/hosting/wiki.karshi.ca/wp-content/themes</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);"># IMPORTANT !  Try not to modify the original theme. Instead make a child theme of it.</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);">#                          Follow the my notes on the subject or visit </span><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">https://codex.wordpress.org/Child_Themes</span></div><div><span style="font-weight: bold; font-size: 24px;">Creating a Child Theme</span></div><div><br /></div><div># The main reason why we want to work with the Child Theme rather than the original is</div><div># that if the original Theme gets update, all our mdification in the Theme will be gone!</div><div># An other reason, we want to use the child theme to modify is that if we screwed up with</div><div># our changes, we easily recover my replacing the parent code.</div><div># Don’t follow anyone’s instruction untill you read the <span style="color: rgb(255, 47, 146);"> </span><span style="color: rgb(4, 51, 255);">https://codex.wordpress.org/Child_Themes</span></div><div># The WordPress constantly keep improving the way its done. </div><div><br /></div><div>Step 1: Create the Child Theme and setup the permissions</div><div>           =&gt; cd /opt/hosting/wiki.karshi.ca/wp-content/themes</div><div>          # You must append “-child” to the Theme folder !</div><div>           =&gt; sudo mkdir wikiwp-child</div><div>           =&gt; sudo chown -R www:www  wikiwp-child</div><div><br /></div><div>Step 2: The most important files to be present in the child theme:</div><div>            “style.css”  and “functions.php”</div><div><br /></div><div>            Requirements from the “style.css” to be valid :</div><div>            —————————— style.css file ————————</div><div>            /*</div><div>            <span style="color: rgb(146, 144, 0);">Theme Name</span>: KFH-Wiki</div><div>           <span style="color: rgb(146, 144, 0);"> Theme URI:</span> <a href="https://wikiwp.com/">https://wikiwp.com/</a></div><div>            <span style="color: rgb(146, 144, 0);">Description</span>: This is a child theme of WikiWP 2018 ( Version 1.8.2 )</div><div>           <span style="color: rgb(146, 144, 0);"> Author</span>: Karshi Hasanov</div><div>            <span style="color: rgb(146, 144, 0);">Author URI</span>: <a href="http://www.karshi.ca">www.karshi.ca</a></div><div>            <span style="color: rgb(146, 144, 0);">Template</span>: wikiwp</div><div>           <span style="color: rgb(146, 144, 0);"> Version</span>: 0.1</div><div>            */</div><div>           ————————————————————————-  </div><div><br /></div><div>            <font color="#929292">Note: The “Template” must have the exact name of the original theme under “/wp-content/themes”.</font></div><div><font color="#929292">                      My version of the theme nothing to do with the orginal version. In the above example,</font></div><div><font color="#929292">                      the original version is 1.8.2 and mine 0.1</font></div><div><font color="#929292"><br /></font></div><div><font color="#929292">            The “functions.php” needs to load the CSS stylesheet files. I don’t get into details here.</font></div><div><font color="#929292">            You have to read the parents “functions.php” file to see what CSS files are getting loaded.</font></div><div><font color="#929292">            If you don’t include those CSS’s you might end up ugly looking site.</font></div><div>            ——————————————— functions.php file —————————————————————</div><div><br /></div><div>            <span style="font-weight: bold;">&lt;?php</span></div><div>            <span style="font-weight: bold;">function</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 150, 255);"> kfh_theme_enqueue_styles()</span> {</div><div><br /></div><div>                  <font color="#009193"> wp_enqueue_style(</font>'bootstrap-style',get_template_directory_uri() . '/css/bootstrap.min.css');</div><div>                   <font color="#009193">wp_enqueue_style</font>('wikiwp-style',get_template_directory_uri() . '/style.css');</div><div>                  <font color="#009193"> wp_enqueue_style</font>('wiki-style',get_template_directory_uri() . '/css/wiki.css');</div><div>                   <font color="#009193">wp_enqueue_style</font>('navigation-side-style',get_template_directory_uri() . '/css/navigation-side.css');</div><div>                    );</div><div>            }</div><div>            <span style="font-weight: bold;">add_action</span>( '<span style="color: rgb(0, 145, 147);">wp_enqueue_scripts</span>', ‘<span style="color: rgb(0, 150, 255);">kfh_theme_enqueue_styles</span>' );</div><div>            <span style="font-weight: bold;">?&gt;</span></div><div>            ————————————————————————————————————————————</div><div><br /></div><div>            Note: Here we are dealing only with the parent’s  CSS found in its "functions.php” file. We did not modify</div><div>                      the child “style.css” yet. If we do so, we have to let the functions.php to include it !</div><div><span>    <span>    <span>    <span>    <span>    <span>  Till now we have an identical theme. No modification made yet.</span></span></span></span></span></span><br /></div><div><span><span><span><span><span><span><br /></span></span></span></span></span></span></div><div><span><span><span><span><span><span><br /></span></span></span></span></span></span></div><div><span><span><span><span><span><span>           Modifying the Child Theme</span></span></span></span></span></span></div><div><br /></div><div>           # The first step to modify our child theme is that we have to include the child “style.css” to our </div><div>           # “functions.php”. Other wise, no change will take effect.</div><div><br /></div><div>                     </div><div><br /></div></en-note>